<HEADLINE>
<P>
WALTER MARTIN; ORANGE COUNTY RADIO MINISTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Walter Martin, a Baptist minister whose radio show "The Bible Answer Man," was 
heard across the country, died Monday at his San Juan Capistrano home at age 60 
of a heart attack. 
</P>
<P>
Heard in Orange County on KKLA-FM and in more than 100 other markets 
nationwide, Martin was considered an authority on the Bible and said his 
mission was to confront "cults" and "unbiblical beliefs." 
</P>
<P>
Martin founded his Christian Research Institute in 1960. The Irvine-based group 
started "The Bible Answer Man" four years later in New Jersey and moved it to 
Southern California in 1974. 
</P>
<P>
Martin also was the author of several books, the best-known of which, "The 
Kingdom of the Cults," sold nearly 500,000 copies. 
</P>
<P>
Survivors include his wife, Darlene, and six children. 
</P>
