<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN SENT TO PRISON IN THREATS TO FONDA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man who threatened the lives of actress Jane Fonda and her husband, Tom 
Hayden, has been sentenced to 16 months in prison. 
</P>
<P>
Louis Robert Spallone, 42, of Sherman Oaks, pleaded guilty in May to three 
felony counts of falsely reporting a bomb to the couple. He was sentenced 
Monday by Santa Monica Superior Court Judge Robert W. Thomas. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles County Deputy Dist. Atty. Richard Stone said at a preliminary 
hearing that Spallone made numerous "very threatening phone calls" to Hayden's 
office in 1987 and 1988. 
