<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NAMES IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rob Halvaks, UC Irvine's senior associate athletic director, resigned, 
effective July 10 to become operations manager for Money Radio. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA AT IRVINE; SCHOOL ADMINISTRATORS; RESIGNATIONS; 
COLLEGE ATHLETICS; MONEY RADIO (COMPANY); HALVAKS, ROB 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA062889-0120 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 75794 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 28, 1989, Wednesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part 3; Page 3; Column 5; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
64 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nate Odomes, a defensive back for the Buffalo Bills, was charged in Eau Claire, 
Wis., with possession of marijuana, stemming from an incident Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Jim Heffernan, the National Football League's director of public relations, 
said no action would be taken against Odomes unless he was convicted of the 
offense. 
</P>
<P>
Heffernan said the league has not set penalties for such an offense. 
</P>
</TEXT>
