<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOX PLANS TO BEAT BIG THREE TO FALL KICKOFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE WEINSTEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In an effort to get a jump on the big three networks, Fox Broadcasting Co. said 
Tuesday that it will launch at least part of its new fall season in August. 
</P>
<P>
The upstart fourth network will premiere a new season of "America's Most 
Wanted" Aug. 20. Then on Aug. 27, Fox will inaugurate a new season of its 
top-rated show, "Married . . . With Children," in its new 9 p.m. time period, 
and also will debut "Open House," a new incarnation of Fox's "Duet," at 9:30 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Fox already had said it will present some new programming in July. On July 9, 
Fox will launch a new series, "Totally Hidden Video," for a six-week run. And 
it will air the much-publicized "Cops in Russia" episode Saturday, July 15 at 8 
p.m., with fresh episodes of the "Cops" series beginning the following week and 
continuing through the summer. STEVE WEINSTEIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
