<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
ADDED $300 MILLION OKD FOR TOXICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The House Armed Services Committee today approved an additional $300 million 
for the Department of Energy to clean up toxic and radioactive wastes at 
nuclear weapons sites. 
</P>
<P>
The House panel, on its second day of drafting a defense budget, also accepted 
an amendment requiring the Bush Administration to certify that safety standards 
for the withdrawal of chemical stockpiles in Europe be met before $36.6 million 
can be spent. 
</P>
<P>
Both measures were approved by voice vote. 
</P>
